Here is a complete explanation of why accuracy was 0% and what the fix does:

**The fundamental bug — split design:**

```
OLD (wrong):                          NEW (correct):
─────────────────────────────         ────────────────────────────────────
558 videos randomly split:            558 videos, split by aug type:
  train = 390 unique classes            train = aug_001..aug_019  ← all 558 classes
  val   = 84  unique classes            val   = aug_000           ← all 558 classes
  test  = 84  unique classes            test  = original .npy     ← all 558 classes

Class overlap between splits: 0%     Class overlap between splits: 100%
Val accuracy: permanently 0%         Val accuracy: meaningful signal
```

The model was trained on class set A and evaluated on class set B — classes it had never seen. 0% accuracy was the only mathematically possible outcome regardless of model quality.

**Three files fixed:**

| File | Fix |
|---|---|
| `03_augment_data.sh` | Detects old flat manifest and forces regeneration; prints the new split sizes clearly |
| `train.py` | Reads `manifest['train']`, `manifest['val']`, `manifest['test']` instead of `splits.json`; removed broken `--use_augmented` flag |
| `evaluate.py` | Same manifest-based loading; fixed `torch.cuda.amp.autocast` → `torch.amp.autocast('cuda', ...)` |



